to have Mr. Hai's people take over.

161
00:08:46,660 --> 00:08:47,830
But I'm not sure

162
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:49,590
if Mr. Hai would be interested.

163
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:55,470
In front of those officials,

164
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:57,110
Du Liang bribed me.

165
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:00,830
I had discovered

166
00:09:00,830 --> 00:09:01,630
their secret.

167
00:09:01,830 --> 00:09:02,710
If I refused,

168
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:04,920
I would have made myself
an enemy of all.

169
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:06,560
Soon after,

170
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:07,750
Du Liang wanted me

171
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:08,960
to recommend him
for promotion to the capital.

172
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,750
Once this was done,

173
00:09:12,660 --> 00:09:13,230
everything

174
00:09:13,540 --> 00:09:14,990
would have been settled.

175
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:17,040
However...

176
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:19,590
Yu Qian

177
00:09:20,590 --> 00:09:21,680
was an unexpected variable.

178
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:24,750
Why can Du Liang imprison

179
00:09:24,830 --> 00:09:25,590
so many women?

180
00:09:26,510 --> 00:09:27,630
Can't you see

181
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:28,800
how deep this conspiracy runs?

182
00:09:29,350 --> 00:09:30,960
Don't bring disaster upon yourself.

183
00:09:31,230 --> 00:09:31,920
Go back to the capital with me.

184
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:33,630
Pretend none of this ever happened.

185
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:34,680
Hai.

186
00:09:36,660 --> 00:09:37,920
You and I passed
the same imperial examination.

187
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:39,710
We've known each other for years.

188
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:41,350
I never thought

189
00:09:41,350 --> 00:09:42,440
you would say such words.

190
00:09:42,710 --> 00:09:43,990
We are responsible for supervision.

191
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:45,160
If we turn a blind eye,

192
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:46,400
will the official robe

193
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:47,280
not weigh heavy upon you?

194
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:48,800
Will the oath you made as an official

195
00:09:48,830 --> 00:09:49,990
not burden and ache you?

196
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:52,060
Why are you so stubborn?

197
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:54,560
Is it because you're about
to be promoted to Vice Minister?

198
00:09:55,230 --> 00:09:56,230
Are you worried
about implicating yourself?

199
00:10:00,630 --> 00:10:01,110
Fine.

200
00:10:02,220 --> 00:10:03,470
No need to persuade me anymore.

201
00:10:04,510 --> 00:10:05,200
I swear

202
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:06,940
I will investigate it to the end.

203
00:10:07,420 --> 00:10:08,140
No matter

204
00:10:08,300 --> 00:10:09,260
who is behind Du Liang,

205
00:10:09,510 --> 00:10:10,830
I will not let a single one go.

206
00:10:11,470 --> 00:10:11,870
You...

207
00:10:13,460 --> 00:10:14,960
If Du Liang was exposed,

208
00:10:15,110 --> 00:10:16,040
my bribery

209
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:17,160
would be uncovered too.

210
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:19,350
My career would be ruined.

211
00:10:19,710 --> 00:10:21,440
My family's long-standing reputation
of integrity

212
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:22,830
would be tainted because of me.

213
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:25,800
One wrong decision

214
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:28,320
led to an endless downfall.

215
00:10:31,350 --> 00:10:32,920
There was no turning back.

216
00:10:38,510 --> 00:10:39,440
This is proof

217
00:10:39,560 --> 00:10:41,110
of Yu Qian ordering
the women to be killed.

218
00:10:41,460 --> 00:10:42,200
Hand it to Du Liang.

219
00:10:42,420 --> 00:10:42,920
He knows

220
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:43,680
what to do.

221
00:10:45,510 --> 00:10:45,960
Yes.

222
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:53,710
Yu Qian was an upright man.

223
00:10:54,350 --> 00:10:55,590
He regarded you as a confidant.

224
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:58,110
He had such faith in you

225
00:10:58,470 --> 00:10:59,750
that he even entrusted his last hope

226
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:00,960
in you.

227
00:11:01,220 --> 00:11:01,920
But what did you do?

228
00:11:02,230 --> 00:11:03,400
Just to protect your own career

229
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:04,560
and the so-called reputation,

230
00:11:05,110 --> 00:11:06,560
you let Du Liang kill him

231
00:11:06,590 --> 00:11:07,590
and frame him,

232
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:10,230
resulting in his entire family
being executed.

233
00:11:12,510 --> 00:11:14,560
If Yu Qian knew this...

234
00:11:18,820 --> 00:11:19,990
I have one more question.

235
00:11:22,350 --> 00:11:23,470
You've always known

236
00:11:23,820 --> 00:11:25,630
that Li Zongxu was involved
in the Censor case.

237
00:11:26,680 --> 00:11:28,040
Then what did he do

238
00:11:28,460 --> 00:11:29,400
in Tongquan County?

239
00:11:30,350 --> 00:11:31,080
There,

240
00:11:31,470 --> 00:11:32,990
Li Zongxu

241
00:11:34,060 --> 00:11:34,750
did not only satisfy

242
00:11:34,820 --> 00:11:35,750
his lust for women

243
00:11:36,110 --> 00:11:37,280
and his sadistic tendencies

244
00:11:37,830 --> 00:11:39,320
but also bribed high-ranking officials

245
00:11:39,870 --> 00:11:41,080
and gained the right

246
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:42,750
to distribute official salt
in the capital.

247
00:11:44,820 --> 00:11:45,750
I have another accusation

248
00:11:45,870 --> 00:11:46,960
against Li Zongxu.

249
00:11:47,220 --> 00:11:47,680
Speak.

250
00:11:48,470 --> 00:11:49,280
After Li Zongxu obtained

251
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:50,680
the right
to distribute the official salt,

252
00:11:50,870 --> 00:11:51,870
he exploited it for years

253
00:11:51,940 --> 00:11:52,830
for his own profit.

254
00:11:53,340 --> 00:11:54,160
I found out

255
00:11:54,470 --> 00:11:55,230
that Li Zongxu

256
00:11:55,350 --> 00:11:56,440
manipulated
the price of salt in the capital,

257
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:57,750
making it more expensive than meat.

258
00:11:58,180 --> 00:11:59,680
The poor couldn't afford salt

259
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:00,830
and were even forced
to sell their children.

260
00:12:01,870 --> 00:12:02,470
Mr. Guo,

261
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:04,870
Her Majesty ordered us

262
00:12:04,990 --> 00:12:05,870
to investigate the Censor case,

263
00:12:06,420 --> 00:12:07,300
[Zhang Quan, Minister of Justice]
not the salt case.

264
00:12:07,830 --> 00:12:08,470
Do you think

265
00:12:08,680 --> 00:12:09,320
maybe

266
00:12:09,510 --> 00:12:10,510
we're going too far?

267
00:12:11,470 --> 00:12:12,280
What if I insist

268
00:12:12,350 --> 00:12:12,920
on going this far?

269
00:12:18,340 --> 00:12:19,180
General Wu?

270
00:12:19,350 --> 00:12:20,750
Mr. Zhang, you've long resided
in the capital.

271
00:12:20,830 --> 00:12:22,040
Perhaps you have never seen

272
00:12:22,220 --> 00:12:23,400
the tragedies at the border.

273
00:12:24,110 --> 00:12:24,830
Five years ago

274
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:26,080
during the Battle of Jinyuan,

275
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:27,590
Li Zongxu colluded
with transport officials

276
00:12:27,990 --> 00:12:28,960
because of factional fights,

277
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:30,510
causing salt and provisions
to be blocked.

278
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:31,920
The army was trapped in the city.

279
00:12:32,590 --> 00:12:33,510
Countless soldiers

280
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:35,200
lost their lives because of this.

281
00:12:35,750 --> 00:12:36,960
Corpses and blood
soaked the battlefield,

282
00:12:37,710 --> 00:12:38,680
their armor cold.

283
00:12:39,350 --> 00:12:39,960
Should we

284
00:12:40,470 --> 00:12:41,510
investigate this case or not?

285
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:44,110
General Wu,

286
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:45,590
who else have you uncovered?

287
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:53,080
I have uncovered

288
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:55,080
the officials colluding with Li Zongxu

289
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:56,680
but also found

290
00:12:57,590 --> 00:12:58,440
the Market Commissioner of Changping,

